  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We propose a new approach to four-dimensional Planckian-energy scattering in which we write---to leading order in $\hbar$ and to all orders in $R/b = Gs/J$---the phase of the $\cal S$-matrix in terms of the surface term of the gravity action and of a boundary term for the colliding quanta. The proposal is checked at the leading order in $R/b$ and also against some already known examples of scattering in strong external gravitational fields.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">DESY</subfield>
